<body bgcolor=#ffffff>
<h1 align=center>Qt Xt/Motif Support Extension</h1>

<hr>

<p>
The Qt Xt/Motif Support Extension assists with migrating from old
Xt and Motif GUI code to the more comfortable Qt toolkit.

<h2>Information</h2>

<ul>
  <li><a href=annotated.html>Annotated class list</a>
  <li><a href=classes.html>Hierarchical class list</a>
  <li><a href=examples.html>Example programs</a>
</ul>

<h2>How-to</h2>

<ol>
 <li>Ensure you are using X11R6.
 <li>Ensure the programs you wish to port are compilable by a C++
	compiler, or at least that this is the case for the parts 
	which need migration.
 <li>Decide whether you are writing a new Qt application reusing
	old Xt widgets, or introducing new Qt widgets into an
	existing Xt/Motif application.
</ol>

<h2>Known Bugs</h2>

This extension is under development.  The following problems exist:

<ul>
 <li> The different focus models of Xt, Motif, and Qt interfere.
 <li> Clipboard handling between Xt/Motif and Qt does not work properly.
	This can be solved by using a drag-and-drop selection model.
</ul>

